libpciaccess
------------------------------------------
libpciaccess is a library for portable PCI access routines across multiple
operating systems.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.6-1
  libpciaccess-devel-0.17-1bl1
  libpciaccess0-0.17-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.9.3-1
  zlib0-1.2.13-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.39-1
  cygport-0.35.4-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  libtool-2.4.7-1
  make-4.3-1
  zlib-devel-1.2.13-1

Canonical website:
  https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/xorg/lib/libpciaccess

Canonical download:
  https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/xorg/lib/libpciaccess/-/archive/libpciaccess-0.17/libpciaccess-libpciaccess-0.17.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libpciaccess-0.17-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libpciaccess-0.17-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libpciaccess-0.17-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libpciaccess-0.17-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libpciaccess0-0.17-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libpciaccess-devel-0.17-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libpciaccess)
  /usr/bin/scanpci.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libpciaccess.README
  /usr/share/doc/libpciaccess/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libpciaccess/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libpciaccess/README.md

(libpciaccess0)
  /usr/bin/cygpciaccess-0.dll

(libpciaccess-devel)
  /usr/include/pciaccess.h
  /usr/lib/libpciaccess.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/pciaccess.pc

